Package org.example.scdpro2.business.models.BPackageDiagarm

Class BPackageRelationShip<T extends javafx.scene.layout.BorderPane>

java.lang.Object
org.example.scdpro2.business.models.BPackageDiagarm.BPackageRelationShip<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class BPackageRelationShip<T extends javafx.scene.layout.BorderPane> extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a relationship between two package components in a package diagram. The BPackageRelationShip class defines the connection between a start and end package, including details such as the relationship type and coordinates for rendering. This class supports serialization for persistence.

  • Field Details

    • startPackagename

      public String startPackagename
      The name of the start package in the relationship. This is used to identify the origin of the relationship between two package components.

    • endPackagename

      public String endPackagename
      The name of the end package in the relationship. This is used to identify the destination of the relationship between two package components.

    • relationshipType

      public String relationshipType
      The type of relationship between the two packages, such as "dependency", "association", etc. This field describes how the start package is related to the end package.
